reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 2, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Laptop runs decently. Specs are pretty high for low end. bottle neck is the processor.
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. First thing I will say is that I did not attempt to open or upgrade the device. There is a slot on the bottom that you can unscrew and open but I am not entirely sure what is under the flap. Regardless, the current specifications on this laptop is really nice. The only thing I would say you would want to upgrade but cannot is the processor for sure. This does not do well during gaming. I was barely able to run minecraft on this and it was already low framerate and causing the laptop to really heat up. The laptop is just a 15.6 which is pretty standard nowadays. It is is bit thicker than ultrabooks and does not feel as solid as the ultrabook. The framing feels a bit on the cheaper side which makes me worried about what could happen to it if you drop it by accident. The material is pretty easy to get scratched up so expect it to get scratched if you put it in your bag. The device casing does make it relatively light weight. It does run on a a quad core celeron processor which is on the lower end but does a decent job with basic use. I do like that the ram is 12 gb rather than your standard 8 gb for most other lower end laptops. I am not sure why they just stuck with 12 GB but it is more than enough for what most users need I feel. I am able to handle most multitasking on this device. It can be a good day to day laptop. The battery life on this is okay. On a stress run it was able to last at most five hours on a full charge. The cooling system is not too noisy on low usage but it can be pretty loud if you happen to game a bit with this and push the processor. The vents can be clogged pretty easily as well. It is a bit hard to clean out so be aware of this if you happen to live in a pet home so be aware of that. I am not a fan of the charger as the plug is a thin round plug which can be a bit hard to replace in the future. It does have the power brick is on the end so it does take up the good amount of space if you happen to plug into a surge protector. Be aware that the power brick can get a bit warm during charging so do not put it under anything that retains heat like a blanket. When I booted up of the laptop, the laptop boots up within 15 seconds. It has a big 512 GB SSD which is pretty surprising considering the laptop price. I was expecting it only to have 256 gb. Based on the size, I am assuming it is an m2 drive but I am unsure what is the actual drive. I would say it is definitely not a 2.5 SSD. It has the standard setup for windows 11 and is pretty straight forward. There was not too bloatware. The laptop has max resolution at 1920 x 1080. This is a pretty standard laptop screen size. The screen brightness could be better but it is not terrible. It does not strain my eyes when I use it. I do like that it gives you two 3.0 USB port so you are not stuck with needing to buy an adapter to get more ports. There is also a type c (non thunderbolt) port but I wish it was the charging port to save on space and allow for docks to be used. The laptop can be pushed back for better viewing but it cannot be pushed back all the way. The hinges okay okay. I do not re but I feel like it could break pretty easily if you push it to far back. The wrist rest looks nice with the dark silver, I found it tends to fade over time. As for the keys, they are okay. The keys do feel a bit cheap but they are okay and will work as intended but I am unsure if the keys will fade over time. I could be easy to pop the keys off so be careful. The external casing of this surface is very easy to scratch (seems to be an issue with all this material) so I would recommend that you get a laptop case for it. It is sealed inside a nice bag. The trackpad runs pretty well, It is sensitive and feels smooth to move across. It also does not look like it will wear down easily which is good. There is a camera that will record at at least 720p but the camera feels like it is using the ipad 4 back camera. The microphone is okay but you can hear a bit of choppiness to voice. It does pick up some surrounding noise. It does have 3.5 port to plug in headphones and microphone device. Depending on how much you have open and how much you utilize the laptop capability, you could actually make this laptop last longer. The speaker system okay. Even at max it is not super loud and does not have any feedback from what I can tell. Again this is not a gaming laptop as it does not have a powerful card that allows you to game very well on this computer. The processor speed is decent and it works really well for say school work. There is an HDMI port so you are able to connect this to an external screen. I am unsure if there is a dock that is meant for this laptop. Overall this laptop does give you better specifications than other laptops. You get the same screen as other laptops. It runs pretty decent but it can run warm. Please make sure the vents are kept clear to optimize cooling The battery life is not bad on day to day use. It will last a college student most of the day. The specification is not bad at 12 GB ram and 512 gb SSD drive. The space is more than enough for what a student may need. You are also able to have multiscreen screen if you use type c. You can use an adapter for an additional screen but honestly I am not sure it will be well supported. I am not sure there is a dock that will work for it. I wish the laptop charger was type c and not the flimsy circular plug.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Solid value, great for basic tasks.
reviews.reviewText: This laptop truly shines in terms of value with its price point. While laptops often come with hefty price tags, this specific model does a great job in delivering exceptional quality without compromising on affordability. It comes with a 15.6-inch display which is bigger than many screens and provides a comfortable viewing experience, whether you're working, tackling school assignments, or simply browsing the web, it's a great laptop that can handle most tasks, even some light gaming.. Additionally, it comes pre-installed with Windows 11, so you don't have to worry about buying an operating system.The keyboard offers a comfortable typing experience, and the touchpad enables effortless navigation. The keypad on the laptop is also a nice feature, most smaller models do not include this, so it's a great choice if you do any work (personal or professional) that requires a lot of number entry.With a generous 512GB SSD hard drive, most users will find it to be plenty of storage capacity. The SSD drive provides quick performance, resulting in quick program launches and seamless browsing experiences. Booting up the computr and loading programs happen without noticeable delay.
